# Umami analytics. Both fields must be set to enable tracking; leave either
# blank to disable. Get these from your Umami dashboard:
#   - Website Settings -> Tracking code -> copy the <script ...> tag, then
#     read the `src` attribute and the `data-website-id` attribute off it.
#
# Why two fields instead of pasting the whole <script> tag?
#   SvelteKit's dev server inlines every PUBLIC_* env var as JSON inside the
#   inline bootstrap <script>. A value containing "</script>" prematurely
#   terminates that bootstrap script and the page fails to load with a
#   SyntaxError. Splitting the tag into its src URL and website id avoids the
#   literal "</script>" in any env value. The production build composes the
#   tag at runtime via <svelte:head> in src/routes/+layout.svelte.
PUBLIC_UMAMI_SCRIPT_URL=https://your-umami.example.com/script.js
PUBLIC_UMAMI_WEBSITE_ID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx
